## M4.5b: branches must be analyzed independently.
##
## Sequential walk would treat `<x` in the `then` branch as moving `x`
## for the rest of the function — including the `else` branch, which
## would then false-fire on `print x`. With snapshot/merge each branch
## starts from the same pre-branch state.
##
## EXPECTED: clean (no diagnostics).

sub main()
  x = make()
  if cond
    send <x
  else
    print x
